      ],
      "message": "build: add optional SECP256K1_BACKEND=ultrafast secondary secp256k1 backend\n\nAdd a single opt-in, compile-time CMake option (SECP256K1_BACKEND=ultrafast)\nthat builds Bitcoin Core against an alternative secp256k1 engine\n(UltrafastSecp256k1, MIT) instead of the bundled src/secp256k1. The default\n(SECP256K1_BACKEND=bundled) is unchanged; all existing builds, CI, and\npackaging are unaffected.\n\nThe alternative engine ships a shim exposing the identical secp256k1 API\n(secp256k1.h, _schnorrsig, _extrakeys, _ecdh, _recovery, _ellswift, _musig),\nso no Bitcoin Core .cpp/.h source outside the build files is aware of the\nbackend change. Bitcoin Core links against the shim; revert by dropping the\nflag (or SECP256K1_BACKEND=bundled).\n\nFiles:\n  cmake/secp256k1.cmake               backend selection logic (new option)\n  src/CMakeLists.txt                  link bundled secp256k1 OR ultrafast shim\n  CMakePresets.json                   ultrafast-bench / libsecp-bench presets\n  .gitmodules                         src/ultrafast_secp256k1 submodule\n  src/ultrafast_secp256k1             submodule pin (UltrafastSecp256k1 v4.1.1)\n  doc/ultrafast-secp256k1-backend.md  backend documentation",
      "committer": {
        "name": "shrec",
        "email": "shrec@users.noreply.github.com",
        "date": "2026-06-05T18:13:52Z"
